<MudText Typo="Typo.h3" GutterBottom="true">Welcome to the expertise analysis survey</MudText>
<MudCard>
    <MudCardContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">The Survey & Motivation</MudText>
        <MudText>
            The purpose of this survey is to challenge the Usage Expertise heuristic. Usage Expertise tries to identify developer expertise of libraries by looking at the usage of those libraries. Everytime you import a library and/or use it your expertise in that library will increase. In practice this means that your understanding of the library increases.
        </MudText>
        <MudText>
            This tool will analyse your python project on GitHub and count all of your imports.
        </MudText>
        <MudText>
            When finished analysing you will be prompted to answer how confident you feel in each of the chosen libraries.
        </MudText>
        <MudText>
            At the end you will be given the full import analysis result so you can see how your own self assessment relates to the amount of imports.
        </MudText>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">About us</MudText>
        <MudText>
            This survey is conducted by Hampus, Tobias & Nicholas from the IT-University of Copenhagen in Denmark as part of our specialization in Advanced Software Engineering.
        </MudText>
        <MudText>
            If you have any concerns or questions please do not hesitate to contact Hampus at haiv@itu.dk
        </MudText>
    </MudCardContent>
    <MudCardActions>
        <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled" Color="Color.Primary" Class="ml-auto" OnClick="OnNext">Start</MudButton>
    </MudCardActions>
</MudCard>


